  "prompt": "What are the comparative legal approaches to money laundering across different nations?",
  "response": "Here's an overview of comparative legal approaches to money laundering across different jurisdictions:\n\n1. United States Approach\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- Comprehensive federal anti-money laundering regulations\n- Strict reporting requirements for financial institutions\n- Criminal and civil penalties\n- Focus on detailed transaction monitoring\n\n2. European Union Approach\n- Anti-Money Laundering Directives (AMLD)\n- Harmonized regulatory framework\n- Enhanced customer due diligence\n- Risk-based compliance strategies\n- Emphasis on transparency and beneficial ownership\n\n3. United Kingdom\n- Proceeds of Crime Act\n- Sophisticated financial intelligence framework\n- Strong regulatory oversight\n- Comprehensive reporting mechanisms\n- International cooperation emphasis\n\n4. Switzerland\n- Traditionally strict banking secrecy laws\n- Gradually increasing transparency\n- Enhanced international collaboration\n- Robust compliance requirements\n- Sophisticated financial monitoring systems\n\n5. Singapore\n- Strict regulatory environment\n- Advanced technological monitoring\n- Comprehensive legal framework\n- Severe penalties for non-compliance\n- Strong international cooperation\n\n6. China\n- Centralized regulatory approach\n- Increasing international alignment\n- State-controlled financial monitoring\n- Developing comprehensive legal framework\n\nEach jurisdiction has unique characteristics while generally maintaining common principles of detection, prevention, and prosecution.",
